x4freetext: -DISTRIBUTION OF NUCLEAR CHARGE AND ANGULAR MOMENTUM
IN CHAINS 132-137, AND 102 OF U-235(N-TH,F) AT
VARIOUS KINETIC ENERGIES AND IONIC CHARGE STATES
HIGH FLUX REACTOR OF THE ILL, IN
SEPERATES FISSION FRAGMENTS ACCORDING TO MASS,
.U-O(2) TARGET WITH A THICKNESS OF 40 MICRO-GRAMS
OR 100 MICRO-GRAMS/CM**2. IN SOME EXPERIMENTS IS
WAS COVERED WITH A NICKEL FOIL OF 0.5 MICRO-METERS
.THE FISSION FRAGMENT BEAM, SEPARATED ACCORDING TO
MASS, IONIC CHARGE, AND KINETIC ENERGY BY LOHENGRIN,
IS STOPPED IN A FAST TRANSPORT TAPE. THE FISSION
FRAGMENTS ARE THEN TRANSPORTED TO A SHIELDED AND
ABSOLUTELY CALIBRATED POSITION AT A GE(LI) DETECTOR.
.FRACTIONAL YIELDS ARE OBTAINED FROM ABSOLUTE COUNTING
OF A DESCENDENT WITH A FRACTIONAL CUMULATIVE YIELD
NEARLY EQUAL TO UNITY, OR FROM DIRECT COUNTING WITH
A SOLID STATE DETECTOR OF THE TOTAL NUMBER OF
SURFACE BARRIER DETECTOR FOR DIRECT COUNTING
OF TOTAL NUMBER OF FRAGMENTS IN THE BEAM. NO FURTHER
DECAY GAMMAS OF THE FISSION PRODUCTS.
.FISSION FRAGMENT ENERGY LOSSES IN THE SOURCE. THIS IS
DONE BY MEASURING THE BEAM INTENSITY AS A FUNCTION
OF THE KINETIC ENERGY AND COMPARING THE MAXIMUM OF
THE DISTRIBUTION WITH THE MOST PROBABLE KINETIC
ENERGY OF THE SAME MASS AS OBTAINED BY SCHMITT,NEILER
.FOR GROWTH AND DECAY DURING COLLECTION, TRANSPORT
ALL DECAY-DATA ARE TAKEN FROM TABLE 1 OF MAIN
A.P.T. JAPAN CODE CHANGED TO JPN
